206 void ClassDefImpl::init(const char *defFileName, const char *name,
207  const QCString &ctStr, const char *fName)
208 {
209  if (fName)
210  {
211  fileName=stripExtension(fName);
212  }
213  else
214  {
215  fileName=ctStr+name;
216  }
217  exampleSDict = 0;
218  inherits = 0;
219  inheritedBy = 0;
220  allMemberNameInfoSDict = 0;
221  incInfo=0;
222  tempArgs=0;
223  typeConstraints=0;
224  prot=Public;
225  nspace=0;
226  fileDef=0;
227  usesImplClassDict=0;
228  usedByImplClassDict=0;
229  usesIntfClassDict=0;
230  constraintClassDict=0;
231  memberGroupSDict = 0;
232  innerClasses = 0;
233  subGrouping=Config_getBool(SUBGROUPING);
234  templateInstances = 0;
235  variableInstances = 0;
236  templateMaster =0;
237  templBaseClassNames = 0;
238  isAbstract = FALSE;
239  isStatic = FALSE;
240  isTemplArg = FALSE;
241  membersMerged = FALSE;
242  categoryOf = 0;
243  usedOnly = FALSE;
244  isSimple = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
245  arrowOperator = 0;
246  taggedInnerClasses = 0;
247  tagLessRef = 0;
248  spec=0;
249  //QCString ns;
250  //extractNamespaceName(name,className,ns);
251  //printf("m_name=%s m_className=%s ns=%s\n",m_name.data(),m_className.data(),ns.data());
252 
253  // we cannot use getLanguage at this point, as setLanguage has not been called.
254  SrcLangExt lang = getLanguageFromFileName(defFileName);
255  if ((lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp || lang==SrcLangExt_ObjC) &&
256  guessSection(defFileName)==Entry::SOURCE_SEC)
257  {
258  isLocal=TRUE;
259  }
260  else
261  {
262  isLocal=FALSE;
263  }
264  isGeneric = (lang==SrcLangExt_CSharp || lang==SrcLangExt_Java) && QCString(name).find('<')!=-1;
265  isAnonymous = QCString(name).find('@')!=-1;
266 }

295 ClassDef::ClassDef(
296  const char *defFileName,int defLine,int defColumn,
297  const char *nm,CompoundType ct,

299  bool isSymbol,bool isJavaEnum)

311  if (!lref)

328 QCString ClassDef::displayName(bool includeScope) const
329 {
330  //static bool optimizeOutputForJava = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_JAVA);
331  SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
332  //static bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
333  QCString n;
334  if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
335  {
336  n = VhdlDocGen::getClassName(this);
337  }
338  else
339  {
340  if (includeScope)
341  {
342  n=qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
343  }
344  else
345  {
346  n=className();
347  }
348  }
349  QCString sep=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
350  if (sep!="::")
351  {
352  n=substitute(n,"::",sep);
353  }
354  if (m_impl->compType==ClassDef::Protocol && n.right(2)=="-p")
355  {
356  n="<"+n.left(n.length()-2)+">";
357  }
358  //else if (n.right(2)=="-g")
359  //{
360  // n = n.left(n.length()-2);
361  //}
362  //printf("ClassDef::displayName()=%s\n",n.data());
363  if (n.find('@')!=-1)
364  {
365  return removeAnonymousScopes(n);
366  }
367  else
368  {
369  return n;
370  }
371 }

374 void ClassDef::insertBaseClass(ClassDef *cd,const char *n,Protection p,
375  Specifier s,const char *t)
376 {
377  //printf("*** insert base class %s into %s\n",cd->name().data(),name().data());

382  m_impl->inherits->setAutoDelete(TRUE);

384  m_impl->inherits->append(new BaseClassDef(cd,n,p,s,t));
385  m_impl->isSimple = FALSE;

388 // inserts a derived/sub class in the inherited-by list
389 void ClassDef::insertSubClass(ClassDef *cd,Protection p,
390  Specifier s,const char *t)
391 {
392  //printf("*** insert sub class %s into %s\n",cd->name().data(),name().data());
393  static bool extractPrivate = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIVATE);
394  if (!extractPrivate && cd->protection()==Private) return;
395  if (m_impl->inheritedBy==0)
396  {
397  m_impl->inheritedBy = new BaseClassList;
398  m_impl->inheritedBy->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
399  }
400  m_impl->inheritedBy->inSort(new BaseClassDef(cd,0,p,s,t));
401  m_impl->isSimple = FALSE;
402 }

404 void ClassDef::addMembersToMemberGroup()
405 {
406  QListIterator<MemberList> mli(m_impl->memberLists);
407  MemberList *ml;
408  for (mli.toFirst();(ml=mli.current());++mli)
409  {
410  if ((ml->listType()&MemberListType_detailedLists)==0)
411  {
412  ::addMembersToMemberGroup(ml,&m_impl->memberGroupSDict,this);
413  }
414  }
415 
416  // add members inside sections to their groups
417  if (m_impl->memberGroupSDict)
418  {
419  MemberGroupSDict::Iterator mgli(*m_impl->memberGroupSDict);
420  MemberGroup *mg;
421  for (;(mg=mgli.current());++mgli)
422  {
423  if (mg->allMembersInSameSection() && m_impl->subGrouping)
424  {
425  //printf("addToDeclarationSection(%s)\n",mg->header().data());
426  mg->addToDeclarationSection();
427  }
428  }
429  }
430 }

432 // adds new member definition to the class
433 void ClassDef::internalInsertMember(MemberDef *md,
434  Protection prot,
435  bool addToAllList
436  )
437 {
438  //printf("insertInternalMember(%s) isHidden()=%d\n",md->name().data(),md->isHidden());
439  if (md->isHidden()) return;
440 
441  if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
442  {
443  QCString title=VhdlDocGen::trVhdlType(md->getMemberSpecifiers(),FALSE);
444  if (!m_impl->vhdlSummaryTitles.find(title))
445  {
446  m_impl->vhdlSummaryTitles.append(title,new QCString(title));
447  }
448  }
449 
450  if (1 ) // changed to 1 for showing members of external
451  // classes when HAVE_DOT and UML_LOOK are enabled.
452  {
453  bool isSimple=FALSE;
454 
455  /********************************************/
456  /* insert member in the declaration section */
457  /********************************************/
458  if (md->isRelated() && protectionLevelVisible(prot))
459  {
460  addMemberToList(MemberListType_related,md,TRUE);
461  }
462  else if (md->isFriend())
463  {
464  addMemberToList(MemberListType_friends,md,TRUE);
465  }
466  else
467  {
468  switch (md->memberType())
469  {
470  case MemberType_Service: // UNO IDL
471  addMemberToList(MemberListType_services,md,TRUE);
472  break;
473  case MemberType_Interface: // UNO IDL
474  addMemberToList(MemberListType_interfaces,md,TRUE);
475  break;
476  case MemberType_Signal: // Qt specific
477  addMemberToList(MemberListType_signals,md,TRUE);
478  break;
479  case MemberType_DCOP: // KDE2 specific
480  addMemberToList(MemberListType_dcopMethods,md,TRUE);
481  break;
482  case MemberType_Property:
483  addMemberToList(MemberListType_properties,md,TRUE);
484  break;
485  case MemberType_Event:
486  addMemberToList(MemberListType_events,md,TRUE);
487  break;
488  case MemberType_Slot: // Qt specific
489  switch (prot)
490  {
491  case Protected:
492  case Package: // slots in packages are not possible!
493  addMemberToList(MemberListType_proSlots,md,TRUE);
494  break;
495  case Public:
496  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubSlots,md,TRUE);
497  break;
498  case Private:
499  addMemberToList(MemberListType_priSlots,md,TRUE);
500  break;
501  }
502  break;
503  default: // any of the other members
504  if (md->isStatic())
505  {
506  if (md->isVariable())
507  {
508  switch (prot)
509  {
510  case Protected:
511  addMemberToList(MemberListType_proStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
512  break;
513  case Package:
514  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
515  break;
516  case Public:
517  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
518  break;
519  case Private:
520  addMemberToList(MemberListType_priStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
521  break;
522  }
523  }
524  else // function
525  {
526  switch (prot)
527  {
528  case Protected:
529  addMemberToList(MemberListType_proStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
530  break;
531  case Package:
532  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
533  break;
534  case Public:
535  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
536  break;
537  case Private:
538  addMemberToList(MemberListType_priStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
539  break;
540  }
541  }
542  }
543  else // not static
544  {
545  if (md->isVariable())
546  {
547  switch (prot)
548  {
549  case Protected:
550  addMemberToList(MemberListType_proAttribs,md,TRUE);
551  break;
552  case Package:
553  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacAttribs,md,TRUE);
554  break;
555  case Public:
556  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubAttribs,md,TRUE);
557  isSimple=!md->isFunctionPtr();
558  break;
559  case Private:
560  addMemberToList(MemberListType_priAttribs,md,TRUE);
561  break;
562  }
563  }
564  else if (md->isTypedef() || md->isEnumerate() || md->isEnumValue())
565  {
566  switch (prot)
567  {
568  case Protected:
569  addMemberToList(MemberListType_proTypes,md,TRUE);
570  break;
571  case Package:
572  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacTypes,md,TRUE);
573  break;
574  case Public:
575  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubTypes,md,TRUE);
576  isSimple=!md->isEnumerate() &&
577  !md->isEnumValue() &&
578  QCString(md->typeString()).find(")(")==-1; // func ptr typedef
579  break;
580  case Private:
581  addMemberToList(MemberListType_priTypes,md,TRUE);
582  break;
583  }
584  }
585  else // member function
586  {
587  switch (prot)
588  {
589  case Protected:
590  addMemberToList(MemberListType_proMethods,md,TRUE);
591  break;
592  case Package:
593  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacMethods,md,TRUE);
594  break;
595  case Public:
596  addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubMethods,md,TRUE);
597  break;
598  case Private:
599  addMemberToList(MemberListType_priMethods,md,TRUE);
600  break;
601  }
602  }
603  }
604  break;
605  }
606  }
607  if (!isSimple) // not a simple field -> not a simple struct
608  {
609  m_impl->isSimple = FALSE;
610  }
611  //printf("adding %s simple=%d total_simple=%d\n",name().data(),isSimple,m_impl->isSimple);
612 
613  /*******************************************************/
614  /* insert member in the detailed documentation section */
615  /*******************************************************/
616  if ((md->isRelated() && protectionLevelVisible(prot)) || md->isFriend())
617  {
618  addMemberToList(MemberListType_relatedMembers,md,FALSE);
619  }
620  else
621  {
622  switch (md->memberType())
623  {
624  case MemberType_Service: // UNO IDL
625  addMemberToList(MemberListType_serviceMembers,md,FALSE);
626  break;
627  case MemberType_Interface: // UNO IDL
628  addMemberToList(MemberListType_interfaceMembers,md,FALSE);
629  break;
630  case MemberType_Property:
631  addMemberToList(MemberListType_propertyMembers,md,FALSE);
632  break;
633  case MemberType_Event:
634  addMemberToList(MemberListType_eventMembers,md,FALSE);
635  break;
636  case MemberType_Signal: // fall through
637  case MemberType_DCOP:
638  addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
639  break;
640  case MemberType_Slot:
641  if (protectionLevelVisible(prot))
642  {
643  addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
644  }
645  break;
646  default: // any of the other members
647  if (protectionLevelVisible(prot))
648  {
649  switch (md->memberType())
650  {
651  case MemberType_Typedef:
652  addMemberToList(MemberListType_typedefMembers,md,FALSE);
653  break;
654  case MemberType_Enumeration:
655  addMemberToList(MemberListType_enumMembers,md,FALSE);
656  break;
657  case MemberType_EnumValue:
658  addMemberToList(MemberListType_enumValMembers,md,FALSE);
659  break;
660  case MemberType_Function:
661  if (md->isConstructor() || md->isDestructor())
662  {
663  MemberList *ml = createMemberList(MemberListType_constructors);
664  ml->append(md);
665  }
666  else
667  {
668  addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
669  }
670  break;
671  case MemberType_Variable:
672  addMemberToList(MemberListType_variableMembers,md,FALSE);
673  break;
674  default:
675  err("Unexpected member type %d found!\n",md->memberType());
676  }
677  }
678  break;
679  }
680  }
681 
682  /*************************************************/
683  /* insert member in the appropriate member group */
684  /*************************************************/
685  // Note: this must be done AFTER inserting the member in the
686  // regular groups
687  //addMemberToGroup(md,groupId);
688 
689  }
690 
691  if (md->virtualness()==Pure)
692  {
693  m_impl->isAbstract=TRUE;
694  }
695 
696  if (md->name()=="operator->")
697  {
698  m_impl->arrowOperator=md;
699  }
700 
701  //::addClassMemberNameToIndex(md);
702  if (addToAllList &&
703  !(Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS) &&
704  md->isFriend() &&
705  (QCString(md->typeString())=="friend class" ||
706  QCString(md->typeString())=="friend struct" ||
707  QCString(md->typeString())=="friend union")))
708  {
709  //printf("=======> adding member %s to class %s\n",md->name().data(),name().data());
710  MemberInfo *mi = new MemberInfo((MemberDef *)md,
711  prot,md->virtualness(),FALSE);
712  MemberNameInfo *mni=0;
713  if (m_impl->allMemberNameInfoSDict==0)
714  {
715  m_impl->allMemberNameInfoSDict = new MemberNameInfoSDict(17);
716  m_impl->allMemberNameInfoSDict->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
717  }
718  if ((mni=m_impl->allMemberNameInfoSDict->find(md->name())))
719  {
720  mni->append(mi);
721  }
722  else
723  {
724  mni = new MemberNameInfo(md->name());
725  mni->append(mi);
726  m_impl->allMemberNameInfoSDict->append(mni->memberName(),mni);
727  }
728  }
729 }

816 static void writeInheritanceSpecifier(OutputList &ol,BaseClassDef *bcd)
817 {
818  if (bcd->prot!=Public || bcd->virt!=Normal)
819  {
820  ol.startTypewriter();
821  ol.docify(" [");
822  QStrList sl;
823  if (bcd->prot==Protected) sl.append("protected");
824  else if (bcd->prot==Private) sl.append("private");
825  if (bcd->virt==Virtual) sl.append("virtual");
826  const char *s=sl.first();
827  while (s)

877 static void searchTemplateSpecs(/*in*/ Definition *d,
878  /*out*/ QList<ArgumentList> &result,
879  /*out*/ QCString &name,
880  /*in*/ SrcLangExt lang)
881 {
882  if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
883  {
884  if (d->getOuterScope())
885  {
886  searchTemplateSpecs(d->getOuterScope(),result,name,lang);
887  }
888  ClassDef *cd=(ClassDef *)d;
889  if (!name.isEmpty()) name+="::";
890  QCString clName = d->localName();
891  if (/*clName.right(2)=="-g" ||*/ clName.right(2)=="-p")
892  {
893  clName = clName.left(clName.length()-2);
894  }
895  name+=clName;
896  bool isSpecialization = d->localName().find('<')!=-1;
897  if (cd->templateArguments())
898  {
899  result.append(cd->templateArguments());
900  if (!isSpecialization)
901  {
902  name+=tempArgListToString(cd->templateArguments(),lang);
903  }
904  }
905  }
906  else
907  {
908  name+=d->qualifiedName();
909  }
910 }
911 
912 static void writeTemplateSpec(OutputList &ol,Definition *d,
913  const QCString &type,SrcLangExt lang)
914 {
915  QList<ArgumentList> specs;
916  QCString name;
917  searchTemplateSpecs(d,specs,name,lang);
918  if (specs.count()>0) // class has template scope specifiers
919  {
920  ol.startSubsubsection();
921  QListIterator<ArgumentList> spi(specs);
922  ArgumentList *al;
923  for (spi.toFirst();(al=spi.current());++spi)
924  {
925  ol.docify("template<");
926  QListIterator<Argument> ali(*al);
927  Argument *a;
928  while ((a=ali.current()))
929  {
930  ol.docify(a->type);
931  if (!a->name.isEmpty())
932  {
933  ol.docify(" ");
934  ol.docify(a->name);
935  }
936  if (a->defval.length()!=0)
937  {
938  ol.docify(" = ");
939  ol.docify(a->defval);
940  }
941  ++ali;
942  a=ali.current();
943  if (a) ol.docify(", ");
944  }
945  ol.docify(">");
946  ol.lineBreak();
947  }
948  ol.docify(type.lower()+" "+name);
949  ol.endSubsubsection();
950  ol.writeString("\n");
951  }
952 }

1203 void ClassDef::writeInheritanceGraph(OutputList &ol)
1204 {
1205  // count direct inheritance relations
1206  const int count=countInheritanceNodes();
1207 
1208  bool renderDiagram = FALSE;
1209  if (Config_getBool(HAVE_DOT) &&
1210  (Config_getBool(CLASS_DIAGRAMS) || Config_getBool(CLASS_GRAPH)))
1211  // write class diagram using dot
1212  {
1213  DotClassGraph inheritanceGraph(this,DotNode::Inheritance);
1214  if (!inheritanceGraph.isTrivial() && !inheritanceGraph.isTooBig())
1215  {
1216  ol.pushGeneratorState();
1217  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
1218  ol.startDotGraph();
1219  ol.parseText(theTranslator->trClassDiagram(displayName()));
1220  ol.endDotGraph(inheritanceGraph);
1221  ol.popGeneratorState();
1222  renderDiagram = TRUE;
1223  }
1224  }
1225  else if (Config_getBool(CLASS_DIAGRAMS) && count>0)
1226  // write class diagram using build-in generator
1227  {
1228  ClassDiagram diagram(this); // create a diagram of this class.
1229  ol.startClassDiagram();
1230  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
1231  ol.parseText(theTranslator->trClassDiagram(displayName()));
1232  ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Man);
1233  ol.endClassDiagram(diagram,getOutputFileBase(),displayName());
1234  renderDiagram = TRUE;
1235  }
1236 
1237  if (renderDiagram) // if we already show the inheritance relations graphically,
1238  // then hide the text version
1239  {
1240  ol.disableAllBut(OutputGenerator::Man);
1241  }
1242 
1243  if (m_impl->inherits && m_impl->inherits->count()>0)
1244  {
1245  ol.startParagraph();
1246  //parseText(ol,theTranslator->trInherits()+" ");
1247 
1248  QCString inheritLine = theTranslator->trInheritsList(m_impl->inherits->count());
1249  QRegExp marker("@[0-9]+");
1250  int index=0,newIndex,matchLen;
1251  // now replace all markers in inheritLine with links to the classes
1252  while ((newIndex=marker.match(inheritLine,index,&matchLen))!=-1)
1253  {
1254  ol.parseText(inheritLine.mid(index,newIndex-index));
1255  bool ok;
1256  uint entryIndex = inheritLine.mid(newIndex+1,matchLen-1).toUInt(&ok);
1257  BaseClassDef *bcd=m_impl->inherits->at(entryIndex);
1258  if (ok && bcd)
1259  {
1260  ClassDef *cd=bcd->classDef;
1261 
1262  // use the class name but with the template arguments as given
1263  // in the inheritance relation
1264  QCString displayName = insertTemplateSpecifierInScope(
1265  cd->displayName(),bcd->templSpecifiers);
1266 
1267  if (cd->isLinkable())
1268  {
1269  ol.writeObjectLink(cd->getReference(),
1270  cd->getOutputFileBase(),
1271  cd->anchor(),
1272  displayName);
1273  }
1274  else
1275  {
1276  ol.docify(displayName);
1277  }
1278  }
1279  else
1280  {
1281  err("invalid marker %d in inherits list!\n",entryIndex);
1282  }
1283  index=newIndex+matchLen;
1284  }
1285  ol.parseText(inheritLine.right(inheritLine.length()-index));
1286  ol.endParagraph();
1287  }
1288 
1289  // write subclasses
1290  if (m_impl->inheritedBy && m_impl->inheritedBy->count()>0)
1291  {
1292  ol.startParagraph();
1293  QCString inheritLine = theTranslator->trInheritedByList(m_impl->inheritedBy->count());
1294  QRegExp marker("@[0-9]+");
1295  int index=0,newIndex,matchLen;
1296  // now replace all markers in inheritLine with links to the classes
1297  while ((newIndex=marker.match(inheritLine,index,&matchLen))!=-1)
1298  {
1299  ol.parseText(inheritLine.mid(index,newIndex-index));
1300  bool ok;
1301  uint entryIndex = inheritLine.mid(newIndex+1,matchLen-1).toUInt(&ok);
1302  BaseClassDef *bcd=m_impl->inheritedBy->at(entryIndex);
1303  if (ok && bcd)
1304  {
1305  ClassDef *cd=bcd->classDef;
1306  if (cd->isLinkable())
1307  {
1308  ol.writeObjectLink(cd->getReference(),cd->getOutputFileBase(),cd->anchor(),cd->displayName());
1309  }
1310  else
1311  {
1312  ol.docify(cd->displayName());
1313  }
1314  writeInheritanceSpecifier(ol,bcd);
1315  }
1316  index=newIndex+matchLen;
1317  }
1318  ol.parseText(inheritLine.right(inheritLine.length()-index));
1319  ol.endParagraph();
1320  }
1321 
1322  if (renderDiagram)
1323  {
1324  ol.enableAll();
1325  }
1326 }

1582 void ClassDef::writeTagFile(FTextStream &tagFile)
1583 {
1584  if (!isLinkableInProject()) return;
1585  tagFile << " <compound kind=\"" << compoundTypeString();
1586  tagFile << "\"";
1587  if (isObjectiveC()) { tagFile << " objc=\"yes\""; }
1588  tagFile << ">" << endl;

1591  if (!anchor().isEmpty())
1592  {
1593  tagFile << " <anchor>" << convertToXML(anchor()) << "</anchor>" << endl;
1594  }

1596  if (!idStr.isEmpty())
1597  {
1598  tagFile << " <clangid>" << convertToXML(idStr) << "</clangid>" << endl;
1599  }

1601  {
1602  ArgumentListIterator ali(*m_impl->tempArgs);
1603  Argument *a;
1604  for (;(a=ali.current());++ali)
1605  {
1606  tagFile << " <templarg>" << convertToXML(a->name) << "</templarg>" << endl;
1607  }
1608  }
1609  if (m_impl->inherits)
1610  {

1612  BaseClassDef *ibcd;
1613  for (it.toFirst();(ibcd=it.current());++it)
1614  {

1616  if (cd && cd->isLinkable())

1619  {
1620  tagFile << " <base";

1622  {
1623  tagFile << " protection=\"protected\"";
1624  }
1625  else if (ibcd->prot==Private)
1626  {
1627  tagFile << " protection=\"private\"";
1628  }
1629  if (ibcd->virt==Virtual)
1630  {
1631  tagFile << " virtualness=\"virtual\"";
1632  }
1633  tagFile << ">" << convertToXML(cd->name()) << "</base>" << endl;
1634  }
1635  }
1636  }
1637  }
1638  QListIterator<LayoutDocEntry> eli(
1639  LayoutDocManager::instance().docEntries(LayoutDocManager::Class));
1640  LayoutDocEntry *lde;
1641  for (eli.toFirst();(lde=eli.current());++eli)
1642  {
1643  switch (lde->kind())
1644  {
1645  case LayoutDocEntry::ClassNestedClasses:
1646  {
1647  if (m_impl->innerClasses)
1648  {
1649  ClassSDict::Iterator cli(*m_impl->innerClasses);
1650  ClassDef *innerCd;
1651  for (cli.toFirst();(innerCd=cli.current());++cli)
1652  {
1653  if (innerCd->isLinkableInProject() && innerCd->templateMaster()==0 &&
1654  protectionLevelVisible(innerCd->protection()) &&
1655  !innerCd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope()
1656  )
1657  {
1658  tagFile << " <class kind=\"" << innerCd->compoundTypeString() <<
1659  "\">" << convertToXML(innerCd->name()) << "</class>" << endl;
1660  }
1661  }
1662  }
1663  }
1664  break;
1665  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDecl:
1666  {
1667  LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl *lmd = (LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl*)lde;
1668  MemberList * ml = getMemberList(lmd->type);
1669  if (ml)
1670  {
1671  ml->writeTagFile(tagFile);
1672  }
1673  }
1674  break;
1675  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberGroups:
1676  {
1677  if (m_impl->memberGroupSDict)
1678  {
1679  MemberGroupSDict::Iterator mgli(*m_impl->memberGroupSDict);
1680  MemberGroup *mg;
1681  for (;(mg=mgli.current());++mgli)
1682  {
1683  mg->writeTagFile(tagFile);
1684  }
1685  }
1686  }
1687  break;
1688  default:
1689  break;
1690  }
1691  }
1692  writeDocAnchorsToTagFile(tagFile);
1693  tagFile << " </compound>" << endl;

1697 void ClassDef::writeInlineDocumentation(OutputList &ol)
1698 {

1700 
1701  ol.addIndexItem(name(),0);
1702  //printf("ClassDef::writeInlineDocumentation(%s)\n",name().data());
1703  QListIterator<LayoutDocEntry> eli(
1704  LayoutDocManager::instance().docEntries(LayoutDocManager::Class));
1705  LayoutDocEntry *lde;
1706 
1707  // part 1: anchor and title
1708  QCString s = compoundTypeString()+" "+name();
1709

1711  ol.pushGeneratorState();

1713  { // only HTML only
1714  ol.writeAnchor(0,anchor());

1717  ol.parseText(s);
1718  ol.endMemberDocName();
1719  ol.endMemberDoc(FALSE);
1720  ol.writeString("</div>");
1721  ol.startIndent();
1722  }
1723  ol.popGeneratorState();
1724 
1725  // part 1b
1726  ol.pushGeneratorState();
1727  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
1728  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
1729  { // for LaTeX/RTF only
1730  ol.writeAnchor(getOutputFileBase(),anchor());
1731  }
1732  ol.popGeneratorState();
1733 
1734  // part 1c
1735  ol.pushGeneratorState();
1736  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
1737  {
1738  // for LaTeX/RTF/Man
1739  ol.startGroupHeader(1);
1740  ol.parseText(s);
1741  ol.endGroupHeader(1);
1742  }
1743  ol.popGeneratorState();
1744 
1745  SrcLangExt lang=getLanguage();
1746 
1747  // part 2: the header and detailed description
1748  for (eli.toFirst();(lde=eli.current());++eli)
1749  {
1750  switch (lde->kind())
1751  {
1752  case LayoutDocEntry::BriefDesc:
1753  {
1754  // since we already shown the brief description in the
1755  // declaration part of the container, so we use this to
1756  // show the details on top.
1757  writeDetailedDocumentationBody(ol);
1758  }
1759  break;
1760  case LayoutDocEntry::ClassInheritanceGraph:
1761  writeInheritanceGraph(ol);
1762  break;
1763  case LayoutDocEntry::ClassCollaborationGraph:
1764  writeCollaborationGraph(ol);
1765  break;
1766  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDeclStart:
1767  if (!isSimple) startMemberDeclarations(ol);
1768  break;
1769  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDecl:
1770  {
1771  LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl *lmd = (LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl*)lde;
1772  if (!isSimple) writeMemberDeclarations(ol,lmd->type,lmd->title(lang),lmd->subtitle(lang),TRUE);
1773  }
1774  break;
1775  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberGroups:
1776  if (!isSimple) writeMemberGroups(ol,TRUE);
1777  break;
1778  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDeclEnd:
1779  if (!isSimple) endMemberDeclarations(ol);
1780  break;
1781  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDefStart:
1782  if (!isSimple) startMemberDocumentation(ol);
1783  break;
1784  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDef:
1785  {
1786  LayoutDocEntryMemberDef *lmd = (LayoutDocEntryMemberDef*)lde;
1787  if (isSimple)
1788  {
1789  writeSimpleMemberDocumentation(ol,lmd->type);
1790  }
1791  else
1792  {
1793  writeMemberDocumentation(ol,lmd->type,lmd->title(lang),TRUE);
1794  }
1795  }
1796  break;
1797  case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDefEnd:
1798  if (!isSimple) endMemberDocumentation(ol);
1799  break;
1800  default:
1801  break;
1802  }
1803  }
1804 
1805  // part 3: close the block
1806  ol.pushGeneratorState();
1807  ol.disableAllBut(OutputGenerator::Html);
1808  { // HTML only
1809  ol.endIndent();
1810  }
1811  ol.popGeneratorState();
1812 }

1869 void ClassDef::writeDeclarationLink(OutputList &ol,bool &found,const char *header,bool localNames)
1870 {
1871  //static bool fortranOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_FOR_FORTRAN);
1872  //static bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
1873  SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
1874  if (visibleInParentsDeclList())
1875  {
1876  if (!found) // first class
1877  {
1878  ol.startMemberHeader("nested-classes");
1879  if (header)
1880  {
1881  ol.parseText(header);
1882  }
1883  else if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
1884  {
1885  ol.parseText(VhdlDocGen::trVhdlType(VhdlDocGen::ARCHITECTURE,FALSE));
1886  }
1887  else
1888  {
1889  ol.parseText(lang==SrcLangExt_Fortran ?
1890  theTranslator->trDataTypes() :
1891  theTranslator->trCompounds());
1892  }
1893  ol.endMemberHeader();
1894  ol.startMemberList();
1895  found=TRUE;
1896  }
1897  ol.startMemberDeclaration();
1898  ol.startMemberItem(anchor(),FALSE);
1899  QCString ctype = compoundTypeString();
1900  QCString cname = displayName(!localNames);
1901 
1902  if (lang!=SrcLangExt_VHDL) // for VHDL we swap the name and the type
1903  {
1904  ol.writeString(ctype);
1905  ol.writeString(" ");
1906  ol.insertMemberAlign();
1907  }
1908  if (isLinkable())
1909  {
1910  ol.writeObjectLink(getReference(),
1911  getOutputFileBase(),
1912  anchor(),
1913  cname
1914  );
1915  }
1916  else
1917  {
1918  ol.startBold();
1919  ol.docify(cname);
1920  ol.endBold();
1921  }
1922  if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL) // now write the type
1923  {
1924  ol.writeString(" ");
1925  ol.insertMemberAlign();
1926  ol.writeString(VhdlDocGen::getProtectionName((VhdlDocGen::VhdlClasses)protection()));
1927  }
1928  ol.endMemberItem();
1929 
1930  // add the brief description if available
1931  if (!briefDescription().isEmpty() && Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC))
1932  {
1933  DocRoot *rootNode = validatingParseDoc(briefFile(),briefLine(),this,0,
1934  briefDescription(),FALSE,FALSE,0,TRUE,FALSE);
1935  if (rootNode && !rootNode->isEmpty())
1936  {
1937  ol.startMemberDescription(anchor());
1938  ol.writeDoc(rootNode,this,0);
1939  if (isLinkableInProject())
1940  {
1941  writeMoreLink(ol,anchor());
1942  }
1943  ol.endMemberDescription();
1944  }
1945  delete rootNode;
1946  }
1947  ol.endMemberDeclaration(anchor(),0);
1948  }

2642 bool ClassDef::hasNonReferenceSuperClass()
2643 {
2644  bool found=!isReference() && isLinkableInProject() && !isHidden();
2645  if (found)
2646  {
2647  return TRUE; // we're done if this class is not a reference
2648  }
2649  if (m_impl->inheritedBy)
2650  {
2651  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*m_impl->inheritedBy);
2652  for ( ; bcli.current() && !found ; ++bcli ) // for each super class
2653  {
2654  ClassDef *bcd=bcli.current()->classDef;
2655  // recurse into the super class branch
2656  found = found || bcd->hasNonReferenceSuperClass();
2657  if (!found)
2658  {
2659  // look for template instances that might have non-reference super classes
2660  QDict<ClassDef> *cil = bcd->getTemplateInstances();
2661  if (cil)
2662  {
2663  QDictIterator<ClassDef> tidi(*cil);
2664  for ( ; tidi.current() && !found ; ++tidi) // for each template instance
2665  {
2666  // recurse into the template instance branch
2667  found = found || tidi.current()->hasNonReferenceSuperClass();
2668  }
2669  }
2670  }
2671  }
2672  }
2673  return found;
2674 }

2794 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
2795 // recursive function:
2796 // returns TRUE iff class definition `bcd' represents an (in)direct base
2797 // class of class definition `cd'.
2798 
2799 bool ClassDef::isBaseClass(ClassDef *bcd, bool followInstances,int level)
2800 {
2801  bool found=FALSE;
2802  //printf("isBaseClass(cd=%s) looking for %s\n",name().data(),bcd->name().data());
2803  if (level>256)
2804  {
2805  err("Possible recursive class relation while inside %s and looking for base class %s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(bcd->name()));
2806  return FALSE;
2807  }
2808  if (baseClasses())
2809  {
2810  // Beware: trying to optimise the iterator away using ->first() & ->next()
2811  // causes bug 625531
2812  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*baseClasses());
2813  for ( ; bcli.current() && !found ; ++bcli)
2814  {
2815  ClassDef *ccd=bcli.current()->classDef;
2816  if (!followInstances && ccd->templateMaster()) ccd=ccd->templateMaster();
2817  //printf("isBaseClass() baseclass %s\n",ccd->name().data());
2818  if (ccd==bcd)
2819  found=TRUE;
2820  else
2821  found=ccd->isBaseClass(bcd,followInstances,level+1);
2822  }
2823  }
2824  return found;
2825 }

2829 bool ClassDef::isSubClass(ClassDef *cd,int level)
2830 {
2831  bool found=FALSE;
2832  if (level>256)
2833  {
2834  err("Possible recursive class relation while inside %s and looking for derived class %s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(cd->name()));
2835  return FALSE;
2836  }
2837  if (subClasses())
2838  {
2839  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*subClasses());
2840  for ( ; bcli.current() && !found ; ++bcli)
2841  {
2842  ClassDef *ccd=bcli.current()->classDef;

3475 void ClassDef::determineIntfUsageRelation()
3476 {

4055 int ClassDef::countMemberDeclarations(MemberListType lt,ClassDef *inheritedFrom,
4056  int lt2,bool invert,bool showAlways,QPtrDict<void> *visitedClasses)
4057 {
4058  //printf("%s: countMemberDeclarations for %d and %d\n",name().data(),lt,lt2);
4059  int count=0;
4060  MemberList * ml = getMemberList(lt);
4061  MemberList * ml2 = getMemberList((MemberListType)lt2);
4062  if (getLanguage()!=SrcLangExt_VHDL) // use specific declarations function
4063  {
4064  if (ml)
4065  {
4066  ml->countDecMembers();
4067  count+=ml->numDecMembers();
4068  //printf("-> ml=%d\n",ml->numDecMembers());
4069  }
4070  if (ml2)
4071  {
4072  ml2->countDecMembers();
4073  count+=ml2->numDecMembers();
4074  //printf("-> ml2=%d\n",ml2->numDecMembers());
4075  }
4076  // also include grouped members that have their own section in the class (see bug 722759)
4077  if (inheritedFrom && m_impl->memberGroupSDict)
4078  {
4079  MemberGroupSDict::Iterator mgli(*m_impl->memberGroupSDict);
4080  MemberGroup *mg;
4081  for (;(mg=mgli.current());++mgli)
4082  {
4083  count+=mg->countGroupedInheritedMembers(lt);
4084  if (lt2!=1) count+=mg->countGroupedInheritedMembers((MemberListType)lt2);
4085  }
